---
// One idea: memory is finally for the handoff — the machine can out-hoard me
// forever, but it can never hand anything on.
---
<svg viewBox="0 0 560 200" role="img" aria-labelledby="relay-t">
  <title id="relay-t">On the left, a machine hoarding a tall locked stack of records, with no outlet. On the right, a small figure passing a single gilded token into an open outstretched hand — the relay, the handoff, what survives by being given on.</title>
  <!-- the hoard: exact, sealed, no outlet -->
  <rect x="44" y="60" width="90" height="110" rx="3" class="ink block" />
  <g class="ink hair" opacity="0.8"><path d="M44 82 h90 M44 104 h90 M44 126 h90 M44 148 h90" /></g>
  <path class="ink hair" d="M89 52 l 0 -14 m -8 8 l 8 -8 l 8 8" opacity="0.5" />
  <text class="hand-label" x="44" y="188" font-size="13">hoarded, never handed on</text>
  <!-- the handoff -->
  <circle class="ink block" cx="300" cy="80" r="9" />
  <path class="ink spine" d="M300 90 C 297 108, 300 126, 298 140" />
  <path class="ink spine" d="M300 104 C 320 100, 340 104, 360 108" stroke="var(--poppy)" />
  <circle class="port-fill" cx="372" cy="110" r="4.5" />
  <!-- the receiving hand -->
  <path class="ink block" d="M400 108 C 398 96, 406 94, 410 104 C 412 92, 422 92, 422 104 C 426 94, 434 96, 432 108 C 438 100, 446 106, 440 118 C 436 130, 428 138, 414 138 C 402 138, 396 122, 400 108 Z" />
  <text class="hand-label hand-label--accent" x="330" y="170" font-size="14">the relay — what survives is what&rsquo;s given on</text>
</svg>
